Grid Layout:
------------
The CSS Grid Layout Module offers a grid-based Layout system, with rows & Column, 
making it easier to design web pages without having to use floats & positioning.

Row & Column
------------

.container {
    grid-template-columns: 40px 50px auto 50px 40px;
    grid-template-rows: 25% 100px auto;
}

Repeat
------
using normal rows and columns for grid

.container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr 2fr 1fr 2fr;
    grid-template-rows: 100px auto 20% 100px auto 20px;

}

(or)

We can use the Repeat() notation like this instead to simplify;
.container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr 2fr);
    grid-template-rows: repeat(2, 100px auto 20%)
}

column gap & row gap
----------------
.container {
    grid-template-columns: 100px 50px 100px;
    grid-template-rows: 80px auto 80px;
    column-gap: 10px;
    row-gap: 15px;
}

(or)

.container {
    grid-template-columns: 100px 50px 100px;
    grid-template-rows: 80px auto 80px;
    gap: 15px 10px;
}

Grid Lines
----------

Place a grid item at column line 1, and let it end on column line 3

.item {
    grid-column-start: 1;
    grid-coclumn-end: 3;
}

Place a grid item at row line 1, and let it end on row line 3
.item {
    grid-row-start: 1;
    grid-row-end: 3;
}